# Architecture & Design Philosophy

- **Paradigm**: Prefer Functional Programming. Use pure functions and immutability. Avoid class-based OOP.
- **Architecture**: Modular Monolith. Organize by Feature (Feature-First), never by layer or technical type.
- **Data flow**: Unidirectional — root actions flow down to isolated leaf nodes (Tree mental model).
- **Coupling**: Components must be strictly isolated but highly cohesive. No cross-feature imports.
